2007-09-21 11:23 -0400  djerius  <djerius@cfa.harvard.edu>  (a194024ff325)

	* lib/Shell/GetEnv.pm:
	add dash support. turn off default Interactive mode.

	dash is used on some platforms as the default system shell (i.e. it
	masquerades as /bin/sh). dash will suspend itself if it is put into
	interactive mode (via the -i option) and is not connected to a
	terminal. because of this, the default is to *not* put the shell in
	interactive mode. If interactive mode is required, use the Expect
	mode.

